n PL/SQL, Java, and C. They run implicitly when a table or view is modified or when user actions or database actions occur. Triggers can be written to fire when:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid13110295\charrsid13110295 \hich\af1\dbch\af0\loch\f1 1\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx720\wrapdefault{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360 }
